   {
    "en": "Ghostly Wedding Proposal"
   }
  ],
  "description": {
   "en": "In order to mourn those who died without a partner, \"Meikon Ema\" is a votive tablet on which a marriage with a fictional character is drawn and dedicated. Shoichi Konuma is transferred to a rural town where such a custom still remains, but his daily life is corroded by the supernatural after he meets a creepy girl. In the midst of fear and confusion, he turns to the head priest, who shows him the image of \"himself\" drawn on the votive tablet... A Japanese horror about the taboo of posthumous marriage begins."
  },
